by Hatsunia » Fri Nov 27, 2020 6:56 pm

The islanders were able to resist Spanish and Portuguese colonialism in the 1500s (and British in the 1600s) due to the Red Fever, carried by fleas on livestock. However, they were still devastated by smallpox from the colonists. The government focused on isolationism, militarism, and a centralization of the social structure around the nobility, along with the adoption of foreign weapons and military tactics. Knowledge about the outside world was gained via trade with Moroccans. In the late 19th century, the British tried to open the island for trade by force and succeeded in capturing the capital. The government retreated inland and from entrenched positions, engaged in hit-and-run and human wave attacks, leading to a British retreat, but with many losses as well. There were also revolts that caused the military government to fall.

There was a Cold War in the 21st century between the US and China, which were both opposed to the still-existing USSR. The Democratic Party (more of a socialist/white nationalist "Dixiecrat" party in this universe) and the "New Left" Progressive Party became more radicalized after the Great Middle-Eastern War. Increasing economic inequality and unemployment from automation led to the second Great Depression. Chinese investors took advantage of the US economy, the Republican Party became more Christian fundamentalist, and the Progressive Party became directly discriminatory towards white people.
